info.description: [![PyPI - Python Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.6%20%7C%203.7%20%7C%203.8%20%7C%203.9-blue)](https://pypi.org/project/nbox/) [![Downloads](https://pepy.tech/badge/nbox)](https://pepy.tech/project/nbox) ![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Apache--2.0-blueviolet) ## üßê What is Nbox? `nbox` provides first class API support for all NimbleBox.ai infrastructure (NBX-Build, Jobs, Deploy) and services (NBX-Workspaces) components. Write jobs using `nbox.Operators` ## Installation ```bash # on macos find the correct wheel file based on python version: https://github.com/pietrodn/grpcio-mac-arm-build/releases/tag/1.51.1 pip install pip install nbox # on linux pip install nbox ``` # ü§∑Why NimbleBox - Write and execute code in Python - Document your code that supports mathematical equations - Create/Upload/Share notebooks - Import notebooks from your local machine - Import/Publish notebooks from/to GitHub - Import external datasets (e.g. from Kaggle) - Integrate PyTorch, TensorFlow, Keras, OpenCV - Share your projects - Collaborate with your team # üöÄ Startup Program #### If you're a new startup with(<$1M raised,<3 years since founded) then you're in luck to be the part of our startup program! #### Get *$420k* worth of deals on your favorite tools ##### Check it out ! # üéö Features ### üèóÔ∏è Freedom To Build ![Build Landing Page (2)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89596037/181773716-ba63f167-af0d-48aa-921a-02e13238c0f2.gif) ### ü¶æ Automate with Ease ![Jobs Landing Page](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89596037/181774553-99120354-72f5-4064-9216-4f8a5aa050be.gif) ### üöÄ Intuitive Dashboard ![Deploy Landing Page](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89596037/181775468-cc342a30-d87e-4576-8bdd-8ffdd75ff759.gif) # üèÅ Get Started **Install the package from pypi:** When loading nbox for the first time, it will prompt you the username and password and create a secrets file at ```~/.nbx/secrets.json. ``` This file then contains all the information that you don‚Äôt have to fetch manually again. ## APIs Our APIs are deep, user functions are kept to minimum and most relavant. This documentation contains the full spec of everything, but here‚Äôs all the APIs you need to know: ``` nbox ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Model # Framework agnostic Model ‚îÇ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ __call__ ‚îÇ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ deploy ‚îÇ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ train_on_instance (WIP) ‚îÇ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ train_on_jobs (WIP) ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Operators # How jobs are combinations of operators ‚îÇ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ __call__ ‚îÇ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ deploy ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Jobs # For controlling all your jobs ‚îÇ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ logs # stream logs right on your terminal ‚îÇ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ trigger # manually trigger a job ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Instance ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ __call__ # Run any command on the instance ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ mv (WIP) # Move files to and from NBX-Build ``` ### Deploy and run any model Let's take this script as an example ```python from nbox import operator, Operator from nbox.lib.shell import ShellCommand # define your function and wrap it as an operator @operator() def foo(x: Dict): return "bar" # or use OO to deploy an API @operator() class Baz(): def __init__(self, power: int = 2): # load any model that you want self.model = load_tf_pt_model() self.power = power def forward(self, x: float = 1.0): return {"pred": x ** self.power} ``` Through your CLI: ```bash # to deploy a job nbx jobs upload file:foo 'my_first_job' # to deploy an API nbx serve upload file:Baz 'my_first_api' ``` # üõü How to get help? Join our [discord](https://discord.gg/qYZHxMaCsE) and someone from our community or engineering team will respond! ## üîñRead our [Blog](https://nimblebox.ai/blog). # üß© License The code in thist repo is licensed as [Apache License 2.0](./LICENSE).
